race.comment: BELMONT PARK (6) stepped up to this trip and spiked his figures beaten a long neck. He gives away starts but will hit this contest at peak fitness and can go one better. BITTER SPIRIT (3) steps up to the mile for the first time. Missed the hat-trick by 1.6L over 1300m 10 days ago when powering home from back in the field. Gives every indication the extra metres will suit, but is likely to drift back from the inside barrier and need the splits to come. CHANCE (9) beat BELMONT PARK home and is also on the improve. Has to carry more weight, but he may settle closer today. Wiggins sticks with MOOLOOLABA (1), who comes back in class and distance. His effort two back at this track and trip distance was good and he can't be ruled out. KHAMIS (11) won't be far away.
